The Herald Prosper Dembedza Court Correspondent
A Harare man has appeared in court on allegations of defrauding OB Plus Trading (PVT) Ltd of 360 tonnes of maize valued at US$131 400. Hugh Tinashe Sibanda was facing fraud and theft charges when he appeared before Harare Magistrate Mrs Vongai Muchuchuti Guwuriro. It is the Stateâ€™s case that Sibanda misrepresented as the manager and supervisor of OB Plus Trading (PVT) Ltd and was given 360 tonnes of maize which he sold and before converting the money to his own use.
Sibanda was remanded in custody to tomorrow for full bail application.